ormation about your research topic. Encyclopedia articles, historical dictionaries, and other reference books summarize what scholars have already written about important historical events, groups, institutions, processes, and conflicts, giving you context for your own research. Each entry includes a bibliography referring to more detailed sources and can also provide you with vocabulary you can use when searching for books and journal articles.    Credo Reference  Growing collection of electronic reference books -- dictionaries, encyclopedias, bilinguals, almanacs, handbooks, atlases, and directories.   more...  less...   A continually growing collection of electronic reference books -- dictionaries, encyclopedias, almanacs, handbooks, atlases and directories. There are bilinguals, general and specialized reference books, and all can be searched from one interface. See the title list on the website.  http://www.credoreference.com/advanced.do    Gale Virtual Reference Library  Search hundreds of encyclopedias and other resources; especially useful for biography and historical background. This database may not be compatible with Mozilla Firefox.    Oxford Reference Online  Specialty encyclopedias, handbooks, thesauruses and dictionaries; emphasis on American Literature and Western Civilization.    SAGE Reference E-Books  Growing collection of topic and subject encyclopedias online. Note: To search only UIC subscribed titles, please click the Available to me button on the right.   more...  less...   This is a portal to over 60 topical and subject encyclopedias online.                 Guide Author      Jeff Wheeler Email Me           Contact: (312) 996-9373                  Next: Books >>        Last Updated:  Apr 20, 2020 10:44 AM    URL:  https://researchguides.uic.edu/history    Print Page     Staff Login        Subjects:  History    Tags:  daley , history                   Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations  